---
title: "Creating a TidyTuesday Repository"
date: "2023-02-13"
categories: ["#TidyTuesday", R]
---

This post goes over how I created a TidyTuesday repo.

Architectur:

* 2023

  * week_08
  
    * index.R
    
    * plot.png
    
    * README.md

1. Move to your project repository and create a tidytuesday folder. 

```{bash}
#| eval: false
mkdir tidytuesday
```

2. move to tidytuesday folder and create a folder for 2023 tidytuesday projects. 

```{bash}
#| eval: false
cd tidytuesday
```

```{bash}
#| eval: false
mkdir 2023
```

3. move to the 2023 folder and create a folder for week_08.

```{bash}
#| eval: false
cd 2023
```

```{bash}
#| eval: false
mkdir week_08
```

4. In the week 8 folder create an R file called index.R. This will be the R code that creates the graph. 

5. Run the R code to create the plot.png. 

6. Create a readme. md in the folder and fill it out. 

7. Create a readme for the project and fill out info. 

8. Create git hub repo. 

9. Connect to project. 

